{
  "text": "Finally, Algorithm 5 was applied to the elements of T \\F, using the previously computed probabilities vectors p (1) (x), x ∈ T , to get an extension of h of X , as well as its extension to T thu \\F with the first three significant coordinates of Ψ [CITATION_1] , the DM of X in the first time step. As can be seen in Fig 4. 7, most of data is located near the training set while the abnormal data points are embedded far away. ",
